TITLE: Cisco acquires cybersecurity company Splunk in cash deal worth $28 billion
SUMMARY: Cisco said it was acquiring cybersecurity software company Splunk for $157 a share in a cash deal worth about $28 billion.

TITLE: Swiss National Bank holds rates unchanged, ending hike streak
SUMMARY: The Swiss National Bank kept interest rates unchanged at its quarterly monetary policy meeting on Thursday.

TITLE: Sweden's central bank raises rates to 4%, in line with expectations
SUMMARY: Sweden's central bank hiked interest rates for the eighth consecutive time Thursday, as the country continues to battle high inflation.

TITLE: Rupert Murdoch steps down as chairman of Fox and News Corp
SUMMARY: Murdoch's departure comes as his media empire, which includes The Wall Street Journal and Fox News, gears up for the 2024 election.

TITLE: Bank of England ends run of 14 straight interest rate hikes after cooler-than-expected inflation
SUMMARY: The Bank of England on Thursday ended a run of 14 straight interest rate hikes after new data showed inflation is now running below expectations.

TITLE: India suspends visa services for Canadians, demands parity in diplomatic staffing as bilateral crisis deepens
SUMMARY: Canada is currently investigating "credible allegations" that New Delhi orchestrated the extra-judicial slaying of Sikh separatist Hardeep Singh Nijjar in June.

TITLE: Turkey's central bank hikes interest rate to 30%
SUMMARY: The move is a 500-basis point jump from the month prior, as Ankara continues to battle double-digit inflation.

TITLE: 37-year-old quit Amazon and started 20 companies before coming up with Instacart—now he's worth $1.1 billion
SUMMARY: Apoorva Mehta is a billionaire, thanks to Instacart's IPO. But, before the grocery delivery startup took off, he tried and failed with 20 other businesses.

TITLE: Apple Watch Series 9 review: It turns your hand into a button and Siri is faster
SUMMARY: The new models won't be a major surprise, as Apple's wearable still excels at fitness tracking and boasts tight integration with the iPhone.

TITLE: Shares of YG tumble over 13% after report three Blackpink members will not renew contracts
SUMMARY: Members Jisoo, Jennie and Lisa will reportedly sign with other labels, while Rosé will renew her contract with YG.

TITLE: One of Ukraine's strongest allies says it will no longer supply Kyiv with weapons
SUMMARY: A recent dispute over Ukraine's agricultural exports has threatened to break the alliance with its neighbors.

TITLE: Saudi crown prince says Israel diplomatic normalization closer every day
SUMMARY: Prince Mohammed dismissed reports that the two countries had suspended talks.

TITLE: Fed declines to hike, but points to rates staying higher for longer
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve on Wednesday released its decision on interest rates and updates on the economy.

TITLE: Chinese EV maker Nio releases a smartphone it expects at least half of its users to buy
SUMMARY: Chinese electric car brand Nio released an Android smartphone on Thursday. CEO William Li spoke with CNBC in an exclusive interview ahead of the launch.

TITLE: AI is all the rage now, but the gaming industry may not be ready to adopt it just yet
SUMMARY: Some of the biggest game developers in Japan say trends like generative AI and virtual reality/augmented reality headsets for game development may not be ready yet.

TITLE: Hollywood studios, writers near agreement to end strike, hope to finalize deal Thursday, sources say
SUMMARY: While optimistic, the people noted, however, that if a deal is not reached the strike could last through the end of the year.

TITLE: How can you tell if a job is right for you? Ask these 'overt questions,' organizational psychologist says
SUMMARY: "Interview processes aren't set up for us to really get to know each other on a deep level," said Andre Martin. "You have to be an expert question asker."

TITLE: These are the 50 best hotels in the world
SUMMARY: The best hotel in the world is Passlacqua, an 18th century villa on the edge of Italy's Lake Como, according to the 50 Best organization's inaugural ranking.

TITLE: The Fed would be 'flying blind' on interest rate decisions after a government shutdown
SUMMARY: A looming government shutdown could prevent the Federal Reserve from raising rates in November, Bank of America says.

TITLE: Europe is 'very far' from imposing new duties on Chinese EVs despite ongoing probe, top official says
SUMMARY: The European Commission surprised many last week by announcing a probe into Chinese EV susidies.

TITLE: India urges 'utmost caution' in Canada travel advisory as bilateral crisis escalates
SUMMARY: Ottawa is investigating "credible allegations" the Indian government may be connected to the murder of a prominent advocate for an independent Sikh homeland.

TITLE: Ark CEO Cathie Wood says she avoided the Arm IPO frenzy. Here's why
SUMMARY: Ark Invest CEO Cathie Wood said she did not participate in Arm's IPO last week, as the chip designer was overvalued relative to its competitive position.

TITLE: Apple and Goldman were planning stock-trading feature for iPhones until markets turned last year
SUMMARY: Apple was exploring the launch of a feature that would let iPhone users buy and sell stocks, according to people familiar with the plans.

TITLE: Deep-sea mining could help solve the global critical minerals shortage, but it's a lightning rod for controversy
SUMMARY: There are billions of tons of critical minerals on the ocean floor, but whether they should be mined has become a global controversy.

TITLE: Amazon gives Alexa an AI facelift as it launches new smart speakers
SUMMARY: Amazon introduced new hardware and software with generative artificial intelligence features on Wednesday.

TITLE: Elon Musk's Neuralink is recruiting patients for its first human trial
SUMMARY: Neurotech startup Neuralink has received approval to begin recruiting patients for its first in-human clinical trial.

TITLE: ‘Everything Everywhere’ Oscar winner Ke Huy Quan on Asia's 'huge influence' on how Hollywood stories are told
SUMMARY: Asia has a "huge influence" on how Hollywood stories are being told, and that's due to how much the Chinese market has grown, said Oscar winner Ke Huy Quan.

TITLE: 4 in 5 employees in Asia have moderate to high mental health risk, study shows
SUMMARY: South Korea, Malaysia and Japan had the highest percentage of workers with a high risk of experiencing mental health issues, said a Aon and TELUS Health report.

TITLE: Netanyahu says Israel and Saudi Arabia 'can forge a historic peace' with Biden's help
SUMMARY: Biden met with Netanyahu on the sidelines of the U.N. summit and agreed to work toward establishing diplomatic relations between Saudi Arabia and Israel.

TITLE: UK PM Rishi Sunak announces shift on climate policies, waters down targets
SUMMARY: U.K. Prime Minister Rishi Sunak on Wednesday rowed back a delay in the ban on the sale of new gasoline and diesel cars.
